docs.abstract: The offer, which values the British satellite broadcaster at $31 billion, could derail 21st Century Fox’s long efforts to acquire full control of it.
docs.snippet: The offer, which values the British satellite broadcaster at $31 billion, could derail 21st Century Fox’s long efforts to acquire full control of it.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Comcast may have found a way to disrupt Walt Disney Company’s plan to buy most of 21st Century Fox: topping Fox’s bid to buy the British satellite broadcaster Sky with its own $31 billion takeover offer.

headline.main: Comcast Seeks Control of Broadcaster Sky, Countering Murdoch and Disney
headline.print_headline: Comcast  Tries Deal To Blunt  Disney Push

byline.original: By Chad Bray and Michael J. de la Merced

docs.abstract: The neighborhood may be the oldest part of New York, but it feels like the newest with the arrival of hotels, residential and office towers, restaurants and nightclubs that cater to millennials.
docs.snippet: The neighborhood may be the oldest part of New York, but it feels like the newest with the arrival of hotels, residential and office towers, restaurants and nightclubs that cater to millennials.
docs.lead_paragraph: On a recent April morning, the developer Mark Gordon stood in a just-finished guest room in his Moxy Downtown hotel in Lower Manhattan, plaster dust powdering his black pants.

headline.main: Drawing a Younger Crowd to Lower Manhattan

docs.abstract: Legislation introduced last month to better hold financial executives accountable for misconduct probably won’t result in a wave of prosecutions.
docs.snippet: Legislation introduced last month to better hold financial executives accountable for misconduct probably won’t result in a wave of prosecutions.
docs.lead_paragraph: A persistent complaint about the government’s response to the financial crisis has been that the executives who helped push the economy to the brink were not charged with crimes.

headline.main: Why Elizabeth Warren’s Effort to Hold Bank Executives Accountable May Fall Short

docs.abstract: Walmart joined Dick’s Sporting Goods in changing its firearms policy on Wednesday amid a national debate on guns after the school shooting in Parkland, Fla.
docs.snippet: Walmart joined Dick’s Sporting Goods in changing its firearms policy on Wednesday amid a national debate on guns after the school shooting in Parkland, Fla.
docs.lead_paragraph: Walmart, the largest retailer in the United States, said Wednesday evening that it would stop selling guns and ammunition to anyone under 21 years of age and remove from its stores all toys and airsoft rifles that resemble assault-style weapons.

headline.main: Walmart to Raise Age to Buy Guns and Ammunition to 21

docs.abstract: The Federal Trade Commission requires funeral homes to give prices on the phone but not online. A new analysis finds that most do not post their full price lists.
docs.snippet: The Federal Trade Commission requires funeral homes to give prices on the phone but not online. A new analysis finds that most do not post their full price lists.
docs.lead_paragraph: Even as consumers increasingly shop and compare prices on the web, one group of businesses remains slow to put cost information online: funeral homes.

headline.main: Funeral Homes Slow to Put Prices Online
headline.print_headline: Funeral Homes Slow to Put ‘Meaningful’ Price Information Online

docs.abstract: Companies often try to keep digital breaches quiet. That’s something the S.E.C. would like to end, but its guidance may not go very far in changing how companies deal with the issue.
docs.snippet: Companies often try to keep digital breaches quiet. That’s something the S.E.C. would like to end, but its guidance may not go very far in changing how companies deal with the issue.
docs.lead_paragraph: Agatha Christie’s fictional sleuth Miss Marple once said in a BBC adaptation that “good advice is almost certain to be ignored, but that’s no reason for not giving it.” That may reflect how companies will respond to guidance recently issued by the Securities and Exchange Commission about how companies should deal with cybersecurity threats.

headline.main: S.E.C.’s New Cybersecurity Guidance Won’t Spur More Disclosures

docs.abstract: Renée James, who was president of Intel, is gunning for the company’s most lucrative business with a competing start-up.
docs.snippet: Renée James, who was president of Intel, is gunning for the company’s most lucrative business with a competing start-up.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Over 28 years at the giant computer chip maker Intel, Renée James climbed to its No. 2 position, becoming one of Silicon Valley’s prominent female leaders.

headline.main: She Was No. 2 at Intel. Now She’s Taking Aim at the Chip Maker.
headline.print_headline: Intel’s Former No. 2 Aims At Lucrative Chip Market

docs.abstract: Prime Minister Narendra Modi is trying to address rising demands for greater economic and social protections before national elections next year.
docs.snippet: Prime Minister Narendra Modi is trying to address rising demands for greater economic and social protections before national elections next year.
docs.lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — India announced on Thursday a sweeping plan to give half a billion poor Indians free access to health care, as Prime Minister Narendra Modi seeks to address rising demands for greater economic and social protections before national elections next year.

headline.main: India Wants to Give Half a Billion People Free Health Care
headline.print_headline: India Wants to Give a Half-Billion People Free Health Care

docs.abstract: The 73-year-old star of Jill Soloway’s Emmy-winning series will not return to the role that brought him late-career plaudits.

docs.abstract: The move ends an 11-year tie-up once seen as an example of Beijing investment in the United States — an increasingly untenable prospect as relations worsen.
docs.snippet: The move ends an 11-year tie-up once seen as an example of Beijing investment in the United States — an increasingly untenable prospect as relations worsen.
docs.lead_paragraph: At a time when deals between American and Chinese companies are on the rocks, an early example that united a major Wall Street deal maker with the Chinese government has come to an end.

headline.main: China Sells Stake in Blackstone as Deal Scene Turns Sour
headline.print_headline: As U.S. Ties Sour, China  Sells Stake in Blackstone
